[stdout] {"type":"text","timestamp":1772607745919,"sessionID":"ses_3485f15b8ffefS75kAZU5ybKu1","part":{"id":"prt_cb7a79dd0001AKNUl9o401cSTk","sessionID":"ses_3485f15b8ffefS75kAZU5ybKu1","messageID":"msg_cb7a78cad001a3sdniAuC1nWyB","type":"text","text":"Implemented a minimal RP2040 breakout in `index.circuit.tsx` with manual-net connectivity and autorouting disabled via `routingDisabled` on the board root.\n\n- Added JLCPCB-imported parts for core hardware:\n  - `RP2040` (`imports/RP2040.tsx`)\n  - `USB_B10_BRW` USB connector (`imports/USB_B10_BRW.tsx`)\n  - `AMS1117_3_3` regulator (`imports/AMS1117_3_3.tsx`)\n  - `W25Q16JVSNIQ` QSPI flash (`imports/W25Q16JVSNIQ.tsx`)\n- Added onboard status LED path (`GPIO25 -> R_LED -> D1 -> GND`) and essential passive support parts.\n- Wired USB data/power, 3.3V regulation, RP2040 power domains, RUN pull-up, and QSPI flash signals with explicit nets.\n- Kept to non-registry component usage by using JLCPCB imports plus core primitives (`resistor`, `capacitor`, `led`).\n- Executed required build command: `tsci build --site --use-cdn-javascript`, which completed successfully and generated output in `dist/`.\n\nAssumptions used:\n- Minimal breakout focus: USB-powered RP2040 + LED + boot flash, without extra user I/O headers or full production hardening circuitry.","time":{"start":1772607745917,"end":1772607745917}}}

